radiographic_examinations.findings: Fluid-filled, distended appendix with thickened walls measuring 8 mm in diameter, concerning for appendicitis. Mild amount of periappendiceal soft tissue stranding without evidence of adjacent fluid collections. Visualized lung fields are within normal limits. No evidence of pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, pancreas, spleen, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys are normal with no evidence of focal renal lesions or hydronephrosis. No free fluid in the pelvis. No evidence of worrisome osseous lesions or acute fracture.
